{"ops":[{"insert":"Wi-Fi Manager"},{"attributes":{"align":"center","header":1},"insert":"\n"},{"attributes":{"align":"center"},"insert":"\n"},{"insert":"This tool is only available in Linux. It is fairly self-explanatory. It shows the current network connection, if any, and the connection state. You can enable/disable Wi-Fi entirely using the \"Enable Wi-Fi\" checkmark, and for connecting to new networks, you select the one you want from the dropdown in the \"New Connection\" section, enter your password, and hit Connect. Simple but useful!\n"}]}